                         Contributing to Sodglumate

Thank you for your interest in contributing to this project!


DEVELOPER CERTIFICATE OF ORIGIN

    All contributions require a sign-off indicating agreement to the
    Developer Certificate of Origin.  See the file "DCO" in this
    directory for the full text.


HOW TO SIGN OFF

    Add a Signed-off-by line to your commit messages:

        feat: add new feature

        Signed-off-by: Your Name <your.email@example.com>

    You can do this automatically by passing the -s flag to git-commit:

        git commit -s -m "your commit message"

    By signing off, you certify that you assign all copyright in your
    contribution to the project maintainer as described in the DCO.


SUBMITTING CHANGES

    1.  Fork the repository.
    2.  Create a feature branch (git checkout -b feature/my-feature).
    3.  Make your changes.
    4.  Ensure all commits are signed off (git commit -s).
    5.  Push to your fork.
    6.  Open a Pull Request.


CODE STYLE

    Before committing, please ensure:

    -  Code is formatted with "cargo fmt"
    -  No warnings from "cargo clippy"
    -  Tests are added for new functionality where applicable


QUESTIONS

    Open an issue if you have questions about contributing.
